<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title>Common Medications by System</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>Medication Review</h3>
      <p><em>Framework: List &rarr; Purpose &rarr; Taking &rarr; Working &rarr;
          Side effects &rarr; Monitoring &rarr; Interactions &rarr; Patient
          goals &rarr; Plan + safety net.</em></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Set the scene (agenda + safety)</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Expectations : </li>
            <ul>
              <li>&ldquo;What were you hoping to get out of today&rsquo;s
                medication review?&rdquo;</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Concerns : </li>
            <ul>
              <li>&ldquo;Any particular worries about your medicines?&rdquo;</li>
            </ul>
            <li>&ldquo;Any new diagnoses, hospital visits, or medication changes
              since we last met?&rdquo;</li>
            <li>&ldquo;Any urgent symptoms today (e.g., severe breathlessness,
              chest pain, heavy bleeding, fainting)?&rdquo;</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Confirm the full medication list (reconciliation)</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Ask the patient to talk you through EVERYTHING they take: </li>
            <ul>
              <li>meds, </li>
              <li>inhalers, </li>
              <li>creams/</li>
              <li>eye drops, </li>
              <li>PRN meds.</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Specifically ask about </li>
            <ul>
              <li>OTC meds (e.g., ibuprofen), </li>
              <li>vitamins/</li>
              <li>supplements, </li>
              <li>herbal remedies, </li>
              <li>recreational drugs.</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Confirm </li>
            <ul>
              <li>dose/strength, </li>
              <li>timing, </li>
              <li>how long they&rsquo;ve been on each, and </li>
              <li>who prescribed it (GP/hospital/private).</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Check</li>
            <ul>
              <li>&nbsp;allergies and </li>
              <li>previous ADRs(what happened, when, severity).</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>For each medicine: 5 core questions</strong>
          <ul>
            <li><b><u>Purpose</u></b>/understanding: </li>
            <ul>
              <li>&ldquo;What do you think this one is for?&rdquo;</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Compliance</li>
            <ul>
              <li>How they take it ( <b><u>adherence</u></b>): &ldquo;How do
                you actually take it day to day? Any missed doses? Any
                barriers?&rdquo;</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Effectiveness:</li>
            <ul>
              <li>&nbsp;&ldquo;Is it helping? Any targets&mdash;BP, sugars,
                symptoms&mdash;improving?&rdquo;</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Side effects/tolerability: &ldquo;Any new symptoms you think
              might be from it?&rdquo; (dizziness, falls, GI upset, sleep, mood,
              sexual SEs).</li>
            <li>Monitoring/safety: &ldquo;Have you had the necessary
              checks/blood tests recently?&rdquo; (e.g., renal, LFT,
              electrolytes, INR, levels).</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Practical use (especially devices)</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Inhalers: </li>
            <ul>
              <li>check <b><u>technique</u></b>, </li>
              <li><b><u>spacer </u></b>use, </li>
              <li>mouth <b>rinsing </b>after steroid inhalers.</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Insulin/injections: </li>
            <ul>
              <li>check storage, </li>
              <li>injection technique, </li>
              <li>rotation sites, </li>
              <li>sharps disposal.</li>
            </ul>
            <li>Eye drops:</li>
            <ul>
              <li>instillation technique; </li>
              <li>timing if multiple drops.</li>
            </ul>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Whole-regimen safety checks</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Any duplication (two similar drugs) or confusion with similar
              names/strengths?</li>
            <li>Any interaction risks? (e.g., NSAIDs +
              anticoagulants/antiplatelets; multiple sedatives).</li>
            <li>Any falls, blackouts, confusion, daytime drowsiness, driving
              issues?</li>
            <li>Any dehydration/sick-day issues (vomiting/diarrhoea) where meds
              may need temporary adjustment?</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Targeted questions for high-risk medicines (if relevant)</strong></li>
        <ol>
          <li><span style="color: #09a8cc;">see each drug</span></li>
        </ol>
        <li><strong>Shared decision-making (optimise / deprescribe when safe)</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>&ldquo;Do you feel you&rsquo;re taking too many
              medicines?&rdquo;</li>
            <li>&ldquo;Which medicine matters most to you? Which would you most
              like to stop if it&rsquo;s safe?&rdquo;</li>
            <li>Agree plan: continue / dose change / switch / stop trial /
              non-drug options.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Safety net + follow-up</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Explain red flags relevant to their meds (e.g., severe rash,
              swelling/angioedema, heavy bleeding, severe dizziness/fainting).</li>
            <li>Confirm repeat prescription needs and next review date; arrange
              monitoring tests if due.</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <h3>Side effects</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Ask: &ldquo;What side effects are you worried about or
          experiencing?&rdquo; (let them describe).</li>
        <li>Check severity and red flags (rash, swelling, breathing difficulty,
          heavy bleeding, chest pain, severe vomiting).</li>
        <li>Explain common vs serious side effects in plain language.</li>
        <li>Offer remedies/adjustments: dose timing, take with food, add
          protective meds, switch/step-down, non-drug options.</li>
        <li>Safety net: when to stop the medicine and seek urgent help; arrange
          follow-up.</li>
      </ol>
      <h3>Cardiovascular System</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Amlodipine (Calcium Channel Blocker)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs cns endocrine">Ankle swelling (peripheral edema)</li>
          <li class="cvs cns endocrine psychiatric">Flushing</li>
          <li class="cvs cns endocrine psychiatric">Headache</li>
          <li class="cvs cns endocrine psychiatric">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine cns">Palpitations</li>
          <li class="ent endocrine">Gingival hyperplasia (gum swelling)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Aspirin (Antiplatelet)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">GI irritation</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">Dyspepsia</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">Peptic ulcers</li>
          <li class="hematology cvs endocrine">Increased risk of bleeding</li>
          <li class="ent cns endocrine">Tinnitus (in high doses)</li>
          <li class="respiratory emergency cvs endocrine">Bronchospasm in
            sensitive asthmatics</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Atorvastatin (Statin)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ortho-specific rheumatic">Myalgia (muscle pain)</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific rheumatic">Myopathy</li>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Headache</li>
          <li class="git endocrine cvs">GI disturbances</li>
          <li class="git endocrine cvs nephro">Deranged Liver Function Tests
            (LFTs)</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific rheumatic nephro emergency">Rare:
            Rhabdomyolysis</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Bisoprolol (Beta-blocker)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="General cns endocrine psychiatric">Fatigue</li>
          <li class="General cns endocrine psychiatric">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cvs">Bradycardia (slow heart rate)</li>
          <li class="cvs rheumatic endocrine">Cold extremities (Raynaud's
            phenomenon)</li>
          <li class="respiratory emergency cvs endocrine">Bronchospasm in
            asthmatics</li>
          <li class="nephro cvs endocrine">Erectile dysfunction</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Clopidogrel (Antiplatelet)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="hematology derma">Increased risk of bleeding, bruising</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Dyspepsia</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Abdominal pain</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="derma cvs endocrine">Rash</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Furosemide (Loop Diuretic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="General cvs">Dehydration, hypotension</li>
          <li class="nephro cvs">Electrolyte imbalance (hypokalemia,
            hyponatremia)</li>
          <li class="rheumatic ortho-specific">Gout precipitation</li>
          <li class="ent cns">Ototoxicity (hearing loss) in high doses/rapid IV
            infusion</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Ramipril (ACE Inhibitor)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="respiratory">Dry, persistent cough</li>
          <li class="nephro cvs">Hyperkalemia (high potassium)</li>
          <li class="cvs">First-dose hypotension</li>
          <li class="emergency derma respiratory">Angioedema (rare but serious)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Amiodarone (Antiarrhythmic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="respiratory emergency">Pulmonary fibrosis (can be fatal)</li>
          <li class="endocrine">Thyroid dysfunction (hypo- or hyperthyroidism)</li>
          <li class="git">Deranged LFTs / Hepatitis</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Corneal microdeposits</li>
          <li class="cns">Peripheral neuropathy</li>
          <li class="derma">Photosensitivity / Slate-grey skin</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Doxazosin (Alpha-blocker)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs">Postural hypotension (especially first dose)</li>
          <li class="cns">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cns">Syncope (fainting)</li>
          <li class="ent">Nasal congestion</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Spironolactone (Potassium-sparing Diuretic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="nephro cvs">Hyperkalemia</li>
          <li class="gynaecology endocrine">Gynaecomastia (breast
            tenderness/enlargement in men)</li>
          <li class="gynaecology">Menstrual irregularities</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Warfarin (Anticoagulant)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="hematology">Bleeding (major and minor)</li>
          <li class="derma">Skin necrosis (rare)</li>
          <li class="General">Numerous drug and food interactions</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Respiratory System -->
      <h3>Respiratory System</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Beclometasone (Inhaled Corticosteroid)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="infectious ent endocrine">Oral candidiasis (thrush)</li>
          <li class="ent endocrine">Hoarse voice (dysphonia)</li>
          <li class="endocrine General cvs ortho-specific">Systemic effects with
            high doses (rare)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Carbocisteine (Mucolytic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git endocrine cvs">GI intolerance</li>
          <li class="derma endocrine">Skin rash</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Montelukast (Leukotriene Receptor Antagonist)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Headache</li>
          <li class="git endocrine cvs">Abdominal pain</li>
          <li class="psychiatric cns">Neuropsychiatric effects (agitation, sleep
            disturbances)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Salmeterol (Long-Acting Beta Agonist)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs endocrine">Tachycardia</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine cns">Palpitations</li>
          <li class="cns endocrine">Tremor</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific endocrine">Muscle cramps</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Salbutamol (Short-Acting Beta Agonist)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs endocrine">Tachycardia (fast heart rate)</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine cns">Palpitations</li>
          <li class="cns endocrine">Fine tremor (especially in hands)</li>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Headache</li>
          <li class="psychiatric">Anxiety</li>
          <li class="nephro cvs">Hypokalemia (with high doses)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Tiotropium (Long-Acting Muscarinic Antagonist)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth (very common)</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
          <li class="nephro">Urinary retention</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Ipratropium (Short-Acting Muscarinic Antagonist)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
          <li class="nephro">Urinary retention</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Antimicrobials -->
      <h3>Antimicrobials</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Isoniazid (INH) (Antitubercular)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Peripheral neuropathy (B6 deficiency)</li>
          <li class="cns">Seizures (in overdose)</li>
          <li class="git">Hepatitis (dose-related)</li>
          <li class="derma">Rash</li>
          <li class="hematology">Sideroblastic anemia</li>
          <li class="General">Pyridoxine (B6) deficiency</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Nalidixic Acid (Quinolone Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cns">Headache</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Visual disturbances</li>
          <li class="cns">Seizures (in overdose)</li>
          <li class="git">Nausea, vomiting</li>
          <li class="derma">Photosensitivity</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Nitrofurantoin (Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Vomiting</li>
          <li class="respiratory">Pulmonary fibrosis (chronic use)</li>
          <li class="git">Hepatitis (rare)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Trimethoprim (Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="derma">Rash</li>
          <li class="nephro">Can cause a benign rise in creatinine (competes for
            secretion)</li>
          <li class="hematology">Bone marrow suppression (with long-term use or
            in folate deficiency)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Gastrointestinal System -->
      <h3>Gastrointestinal System</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Lactulose (Osmotic Laxative)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Flatulence</li>
          <li class="git">Abdominal cramps</li>
          <li class="git">Bloating</li>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Mebeverine (Antispasmodic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="derma">Rash</li>
          <li class="derma emergency">Angioedema (rare)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Metoclopramide (Antiemetic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="cns">Restlessness</li>
          <li class="cns">Extrapyramidal side effects (dystonia, tardive
            dyskinesia)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Omeprazole (Proton Pump Inhibitor)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Headache</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">GI disturbances (nausea, diarrhea)</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific nephro infectious git">Long-term use:
            Increased risk of fractures, hypomagnesemia, C. difficile infection</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Ondansetron (5-HT3 Antagonist)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Headache</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">Constipation</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine">QT prolongation (with high doses)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Cyclizine (Antihistamine Antiemetic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth</li>
          <li class="nephro">Urinary retention</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Loperamide (Antidiarrheal)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Constipation (intended effect, but can be excessive)</li>
          <li class="git">Abdominal cramps</li>
          <li class="cns">Dizziness</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Mesalazine (5-ASA)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="cns">Headache</li>
          <li class="nephro">Interstitial nephritis (rare)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Senna (Stimulant Laxative)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Abdominal cramps</li>
          <li class="nephro">Melanosis coli (harmless bowel pigmentation with
            chronic use)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Endocrine System -->
      <h3>Endocrine System</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Dapagliflozin (SGLT2 Inhibitor)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="gynob infectious">Genital fungal infections (thrush)</li>
          <li class="nephro infectious">Urinary tract infections</li>
          <li class="endocrine emergency">Euglycemic Diabetic Ketoacidosis (DKA)
            (rare but serious)</li>
          <li class="nephro">Increased urination</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Gliclazide (Sulfonylurea)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="endocrine cns emergency psychiatric">Hypoglycemia (low
            blood sugar)</li>
          <li class="endocrine General cvs metabolic">Weight gain</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">GI upset</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Levothyroxine (Thyroid Hormone Replacement)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="endocrine cvs psychiatric cns General">Symptoms of
            hyperthyroidism if dose is too high (tachycardia, anxiety, tremor,
            weight loss)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Metformin (Biguanide)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">GI side effects (diarrhea,
            nausea, abdominal pain)</li>
          <li class="nephro emergency General">Lactic acidosis (rare but
            serious, especially with renal impairment)</li>
          <li class="hematology cns">Vitamin B12 deficiency (long-term use)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Prednisolone (Systemic Corticosteroid)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="psychiatric cns endocrine">Insomnia</li>
          <li class="psychiatric cns endocrine">Mood changes</li>
          <li class="General endocrine cvs">Increased appetite</li>
          <li class="endocrine cvs metabolic">Hyperglycemia</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific endocrine infectious General rheumatic">Long-term:
            Osteoporosis, weight gain, Cushing's syndrome, adrenal suppression,
            immunosuppression</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Insulin (e.g., Aspart, Glargine)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="endocrine cns emergency psychiatric">Hypoglycemia</li>
          <li class="derma">Lipohypertrophy at injection sites</li>
          <li class="endocrine General cvs metabolic">Weight gain</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Sitagliptin (DPP-4 Inhibitor)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Headache</li>
          <li class="git emergency">Pancreatitis (rare)</li>
          <li class="rheumatic">Joint pain (arthralgia)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Central Nervous System / Psychiatry -->
      <h3>CNS &amp; Psychiatry</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Amitriptyline (Tricyclic Antidepressant)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
          <li class="nephro">Urinary retention</li>
          <li class="cvs">Postural hypotension</li>
          <li class="cvs emergency">Cardiotoxicity in overdose</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Diazepam (Benzodiazepine)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="cns">Sedation</li>
          <li class="cns">Ataxia</li>
          <li class="psychiatric">Dependence and withdrawal symptoms</li>
          <li class="cns">Anterograde amnesia</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Levetiracetam (Antiepileptic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Somnolence</li>
          <li class="General">Asthenia (weakness)</li>
          <li class="psychiatric cns">Mood changes (irritability, agitation,
            depression)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Lithium (Mood Stabilizer)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="General psychiatric">Narrow therapeutic index - requires
            regular monitoring</li>
          <li class="cns">Fine tremor</li>
          <li class="nephro endocrine">Nephrogenic Diabetes Insipidus (polyuria,
            polydipsia)</li>
          <li class="endocrine">Hypothyroidism</li>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="derma">Worsening of psoriasis or acne</li>
          <li class="cns emergency">Signs of Toxicity (coarse tremor, ataxia,
            confusion, seizures)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Morphine (Opioid Analgesic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="respiratory emergency">Respiratory depression</li>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Vomiting</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="psychiatric">Dependence</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Olanzapine (Atypical Antipsychotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="endocrine General">Significant weight gain</li>
          <li class="endocrine cvs">Metabolic syndrome (hyperglycemia,
            dyslipidemia)</li>
          <li class="cns">Sedation</li>
          <li class="cvs">Postural hypotension</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Sertraline (SSRI)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine">GI upset (common initially)</li>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Insomnia or somnolence</li>
          <li class="nephro gynaecology Sexual_history_section cvs endocrine">Sexual
            dysfunction</li>
          <li class="psychiatric cns endocrine">Increased anxiety initially</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Gabapentin / Pregabalin (GABA Analogue)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cns endocrine psychiatric">Somnolence (sleepiness)</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine nephro">Peripheral edema</li>
          <li class="General endocrine cvs metabolic">Weight gain</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Lamotrigine (Antiepileptic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="derma emergency">Severe rash (Stevens-Johnson Syndrome -
            SJS) - requires slow titration</li>
          <li class="cns">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cns">Headache</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Topiramate (Antiepileptic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Paresthesia</li>
          <li class="cns">Cognitive slowing</li>
          <li class="General">Weight loss</li>
          <li class="nephro">Nephrolithiasis (kidney stones)</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Phenytoin (Antiepileptic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Ataxia</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Nystagmus</li>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="ent">Gingival hyperplasia</li>
          <li class="derma">Rash (including Stevens-Johnson syndrome)</li>
          <li class="endocrine">Hirsutism</li>
          <li class="endocrine">Osteomalacia (long-term use)</li>
          <li class="hematology">Megaloblastic anemia (folate deficiency)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Sodium Valproate (Antiepileptic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Stomach pain</li>
          <li class="git emergency">Hepatotoxicity / Pancreatitis (rare)</li>
          <li class="hematology">Thrombocytopenia</li>
          <li class="obstetric emergency">Highly teratogenic - requires
            pregnancy prevention programme</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Infectious Diseases -->
      <h3>Infectious Diseases</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Allopurinol (Xanthine Oxidase Inhibitor)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="rheumatic">Can precipitate acute gout attack upon
            initiation</li>
          <li class="derma">Rash</li>
          <li class="derma emergency">Severe hypersensitivity reactions (e.g.,
            SJS/TEN) (rare)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Amoxicillin (Penicillin Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="derma infectious endocrine">Rash (non-allergic rash common
            in glandular fever)</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="derma respiratory emergency cvs endocrine">Allergic
            reactions (from mild rash to anaphylaxis)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Clarithromycin (Macrolide Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">GI upset (nausea, vomiting,
            diarrhea)</li>
          <li class="ent endocrine">Taste disturbance</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine emergency">QT prolongation</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Ciprofloxacin (Quinolone Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="ortho-specific rheumatic">Tendon damage/rupture (especially
            Achilles)</li>
          <li class="cns">Seizures (lowers threshold)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Co-amoxiclav (Penicillin + Beta-lactamase inhibitor)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea (more common than with amoxicillin alone)</li>
          <li class="git">Cholestatic jaundice (can be delayed)</li>
          <li class="derma respiratory emergency">Allergic reactions</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Doxycycline (Tetracycline Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="derma">Photosensitivity (increased risk of sunburn)</li>
          <li class="git">GI upset</li>
          <li class="git">Esophagitis (advise to take with water, sitting
            upright)</li>
          <li class="ent">Tooth discoloration in children &lt; 8</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Fluconazole (Antifungal)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cns">Headache</li>
          <li class="git">Abdominal pain</li>
          <li class="git">Deranged LFTs</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Metronidazole (Antibiotic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git emergency">Disulfiram-like reaction with alcohol
            (severe nausea/vomiting)</li>
          <li class="ent">Metallic taste in mouth</li>
          <li class="git">GI upset</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <h3>Pain &amp; Rheumatology</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Co-codamol (Paracetamol &amp; Codeine)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Constipation (very common)</li>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="cns">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="psychiatric">Risk of opioid dependence</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Ibuprofen (NSAID)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">GI irritation</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Dyspepsia</li>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Peptic ulcers</li>
          <li class="nephro cvs endocrine">Renal impairment</li>
          <li class="cvs endocrine emergency">Increased risk of cardiovascular
            events (long-term use)</li>
          <li class="respiratory emergency cvs endocrine">Bronchospasm in
            asthmatics</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Methotrexate (DMARD)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git cvs endocrine nephro">Nausea</li>
          <li class="ent endocrine">Mucositis</li>
          <li class="hematology cvs emergency">Myelosuppression (bone marrow
            suppression)</li>
          <li class="git cvs nephro endocrine">Hepatotoxicity (liver damage)</li>
          <li class="respiratory cvs emergency">Pulmonary fibrosis (rare)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Colchicine (Anti-inflammatory for Gout)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea (very common, dose-limiting)</li>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Vomiting</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Hydroxychloroquine (DMARD)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Retinopathy (requires regular eye screening)</li>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="derma">Rash</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Tramadol (Atypical Opioid Analgesic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="cns">Dizziness</li>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
          <li class="cns emergency">Lowers seizure threshold</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Paracetamol</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">Generally very few side effects at therapeutic
            doses</li>
          <li class="git emergency">Hepatotoxicity in overdose</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <!-- Urology, Gynae & Obstetrics -->
      <h3>Urology, Gynae &amp; Obstetrics</h3>
      <details>
        <summary>Combined Oral Contraceptive Pill</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs emergency">Increased risk of VTE (DVT/PE) and stroke</li>
          <li class="cvs">Hypertension</li>
          <li class="cns psychiatric">Headaches, mood changes</li>
          <li class="gynaecology">Breakthrough bleeding</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Solifenacin (Antimuscarinic for OAB)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Oxybutynin (Antimuscarinic for OAB)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
          <li class="nephro">Urinary retention</li>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Tolterodine (Antimuscarinic for OAB)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent">Dry mouth</li>
          <li class="git">Constipation</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology">Blurred vision</li>
          <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Acute angle-closure glaucoma</li>
          <li class="nephro">Urinary retention</li>
          <li class="cns">Drowsiness</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Tamsulosin (Alpha-blocker for BPH)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="cvs cns">Postural hypotension, dizziness, syncope</li>
          <li class="nephro Sexual_history_section">Ejaculation disorders</li>
          <li class="ent">Nasal congestion</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Tranexamic Acid (Antifibrinolytic)</summary>
        <ul>
          <li class="git">Nausea</li>
          <li class="git">Diarrhea</li>
          <li class="cvs hematology">Increased risk of VTE (use with caution)</li>
        </ul>
      </details>
    </div>
